147286.Overview:
Five programs in one!
An animated storybook about a llama named Dolly who is constantly requiring rescue by Jimmy who turns into the many shapes of simple machines;
An adventure game taking you on a search of Tooltown and the Valley of Machines for clues and a surprise ending;
A Coloring Gallery featuring musical markers and a tic-tac-toe game;
A very colorful Maze Arcade challenging you to navigate five increasingly complex mazes while scoring your performance;
And an Interactive Database which uncovers all six classes of simple machines- the inclined plane, screw, pulley, wheel and axle, lever, and wedge.

149661.Overview:
The game contains 4 mini-games representing main events of the baseball match:
Batting Practice to strike a thrown ball with a bat;
Fungo Fielding to catch the flying ball;
Sign Calling 101 to memorize the couch's movements and to repeat them in proper sequence;
Umpire Arguing to make the umpire angrier without getting ejected, selecting the various statements.
Successful player's actions are rewarded with points, and players with more points are enlisted into High Score table distinguished by three difficulty levels. In-game help allows the player to understand the rules of the game more precisely.
